{
  "text": "Microvascular palsies of the third, fourth, and sixth cranial nerves occur in an isolated manner and are relatively common in patients with diabetes, hypertension (HTN), or other vascular risk factors. In these cases, the etiology is suspected to be ischemic [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
